node.text: Just a few hours before the @paralympics Closing Ceremony we catch up with @birgitskarstein - a para-athlete from Norway 🇳🇴 . node.text:
Young, fierce and taking over! From 13-year-old Japanese skateboarder NISHIYA Momiji, who won gold 🥇 to 12-year-old Syrian table tennis player Hend Zaza, who was the youngest athlete at the Olympic Games this year, these new athletes are on fire 💥⁠⁠
⁠⁠
We want to honor these young stars in the #WorldYouthDay. If they have already made history in the first years of their lives, what is yet to come? 🤔⁠⁠

Hit link in bio for more!

⁠⁠
Ahead of Emma Raducanu and Leylah Fernandez's all-teenager showdown at this year's tournament, enjoy these vintage snaps from '99! 😍⁠⁠
⁠⁠
